msgid "FITS, or Flexible Image Transport System, is the standard format for representing images and data in Astronomy. The KStars FITS Viewer is a tool to view those images. It is not designed for editing of FITS Images."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer.rst:11
msgid "The FITS Viewer can be automatically invoked for images received from the camera. It can also be invoked directly from the main KStars menu. To open a FITS file, select the ``File`` → ``Open Image...`` menu item, or press **Ctrl**\\ +\\ **O**."
msgstr ""

